<!--
Top-level README for an eval analysis set. Compiles per-scenario files in the same
directory into a single factual summary.

Voice rules (enforced):
- No sensationalism. No "proves", "dramatic", "remarkable", "clear winner" unless the
  data unambiguously supports it across replications.
- Every cross-variant claim cites a table row or a per-scenario file.
- Single-run claims are labeled single-run. n=1 findings go under "What did not
  replicate" or "Confounds", not "What replicated", unless a prior eval replicated them.
- Confounds section is required when any variant ran on a different version, config,
  or fixture state than its peers.
- "What did not replicate" section is required when behavioral-quality claims disagree
  between runs or scales.
- Methodological note is required whenever sample sizes differ across metric types
  (e.g., n=7 for cost, n=1 for decision quality).

Delete sections that genuinely do not apply — but state why above the deletion.
-->

